name: Brimstone Canyon (North Fork 2)
description:
Approach

Descent

Rap 1: 60ft.

Rap 2: 30ft.

Rap 3: 95ft, 2-stage.

Rap 4: 60ft.

Rap 5: 30? 30=60ft?

Rap 6: 20ft, meat anchor and assist.

Rap 7: 60 25=85ft.

Rap 8: 50ft.

Rap 9: 50 40=90ft.

Rap 10: 95ft.

Rap 11: 95ft.

Rap 12: 75ft.

Rap 13: 60ft?, or bypass left.

Rap 14: 95ft, 2-stage.

Rap 15: 75ft.

Rap 16: 20ft.

Rappel length is rope length, not drop height. All rappel lengths are approximate. Some are only estimated, not actually measured. Numbers provided as a rough guide only. Be aware of your surroundings and do not blindly follow any canyoneering info. Max rap length of 95 feet is an approximation. Also, canyon conditions can change. Bring longer ropes.

Exit

From the last downclimb, it is about 2.6 miles of wash and then alluvial fan to the road.
